{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"compacted_at":1784009854373601007,"compiled_state":{"alias":"animated-dizzied-gosling","assignee":"Joe Oakhart","author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","authorship":{"signed":0,"unsigned":11},"authorship_ledger":[],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-207_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"8309b909-b742-470c-83a4-e3c51bc85e4a","comments":[{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"FORCE_CLAIM: plan-review gate bypassed by user approval — no plan-review attestation was verified. Reason: \"plan remediated over 2 rounds; remaining blocks are fine-grained AC/plan-precision nits on well-understood infra/YAML work (exact container path, bind-mount visibility, BRIDGE_BOT_EMAIL workflow var, verify output-string anchor), not substantive design flaws — folded into implementation. Parent 297d plan-review PASS+signed. Bounding ~17min/round whack-a-mole per config-prune-epic precedent.\".","timestamp":1784004152997984001},{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"[operator-attested] AC2 is inherently post-deploy (the canary runs on GitHub Actions from main on its schedule/dispatch AFTER this change lands; it cannot be exercised pre-land). Concrete attestation of the landed setup: (1) reconcile-bridge-canary.yml (Gerrit change 679) now masks + materializes secrets.REBAR_BOT_SIGNING_KEY to a 0600 $RUNNER_TEMP file, exports REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY, and defaults the committer email to joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com. (2) The signing MECHANISM is proven locally: the canary writes via the rebar CLI, which signs through _seam.append_event when identity+key resolve — and task 9e76's unit test (test_inbound_signing_9e76) demonstrates the same seam path produces an author_sig that verify_event_authorship reports verified against identity 594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d. (3) The bot identity + REBAR_BOT_SIGNING_KEY secret exist (attested on bffe). The live canary-run verification (capture ticket id + rebar verify-authorship = verified) is the bounded post-deploy operator step; no code work remains.","timestamp":1784009715869931001},{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"FORCE_CLOSE: close gate(s) bypassed by user approval — no completion/signature attestation was signed. Reason: \"Setup complete + landed (story 297d is setup-only). The sole remaining AC (a live canary run producing a signed ticket verifiable via verify-authorship) is inherently POST-DEPLOY: reconcile-bridge-canary.yml runs on GitHub Actions from main on its schedule/dispatch, which is only possible AFTER this change lands (the branch lives on Gerrit, not GitHub, so GHA cannot run it pre-land). The setup is done + proven: key injection + bot-email default wired in the workflow (change 679); the signing mechanism is proven locally by 9e76's test (the same seam path yields an author_sig that verify_event_authorship reports verified against identity 594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d); the bot identity + REBAR_BOT_SIGNING_KEY secret exist (bffe). Closing unsigned to honestly signal the live canary-run verification is the bounded post-deploy operator step; no code work remains.\". Session: 8309b909-b742-470c-83a4-e3c51bc85e4a.","timestamp":1784009854373601001}],"created_at":1783968895032458001,"deps":[{"link_uuid":"546a75d0-5212-4f97-a428-d5f6d75f9bce","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"bffe-10c2-1231-41d4"}],"description":"## GHA reconcile-bridge-canary: inject signing key + flip committer email to bot\n\nThe canary writes non-exempt tickets via the normal `rebar` CLI (`rebar create bug` /\n`comment` / `transition` in `.github/workflows/reconcile-bridge-canary.yml`), so it will\nSIGN AUTOMATICALLY through `_seam.append_event` once the identity + key are configured — no\ncode change needed here (unlike the reconciler). The Rebar Bot identity ticket already exists\n(task bffe: `594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d`), so git-email resolution to the bot works.\n\n- **Secure key injection (concrete):** in a workflow step, `echo \"::add-mask::$REBAR_BOT_SIGNING_KEY\"`\n  first (so it can never surface in logs), then write it to a job-local file — e.g.\n  `install -m 600 /dev/null \"$RUNNER_TEMP/rebar-bot-signing-key\"` then\n  `printf '%s' \"${{ secrets.REBAR_BOT_SIGNING_KEY }}\" > \"$RUNNER_TEMP/rebar-bot-signing-key\"`\n  (mode 0600) — and export `REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY` (or set `identity.signing_key`) to that\n  path. The runner's `$RUNNER_TEMP` is discarded at job end.\n- Set the canary's committer email to `joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com` (from the current bridge\n  default) so git-email resolution maps to the Rebar Bot identity.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `reconcile-bridge-canary.yml` masks the secret (`::add-mask::`), writes it to a `0600` file under `$RUNNER_TEMP`, sets `REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY`/`identity.signing_key` to that path, and sets the committer email to `joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com`; the key is never logged or committed.\n- [ ] [operator-attested] A canary run (post-deploy; triggered via `workflow_dispatch` on `reconcile-bridge-canary.yml`) creates a bug/comment/transition whose event is signed as Rebar Bot: capture the created ticket id from the run log and confirm `rebar verify-authorship` (or `rebar verify-identity`) reports it `verified` and attributed to identity `594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d`.\n- [ ] No code change is introduced here (the CLI signs automatically via the seam); the key is never logged or committed.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","bffe-10c2-1231-41d4"],["parent","297d-a233-ce1b-4484"]],"parent_id":"297d-a233-ce1b-4484","parent_status_uuid":"a6021d27-df69-48b3-ba38-e1b0e5d2b801","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"closed","tags":[],"ticket_id":"1787-bbec-7527-4419","ticket_type":"task","title":"GHA reconcile-bridge-canary: inject signing key + flip committer email to bot","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["6a8e86ac-f910-4997-8e07-8ff84b2bd868"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784009854373601007,"uuid":"bc517dcd-db13-4800-be1e-af15673b09c3"}